  "notes": [
    "The Biochemistry major is for students preparing for careers in biochemistry or other fields requiring extensive preparation in both chemistry and biology. Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for this major. To be considered for admission to this major, you must complete the following courses by the end of spring before transfer: One year of Calculus, One year of General Chemistry with Laboratory, One year of Biology with Lab for major (Cellular, Molecular and Genetics), and One year of Organic Chemistry with Lab. Completion of two semesters/three quarters of Calculus Based Physics with Lab, Multivariable Calculus, and Linear Algebra are STRONGLY RECOMMENDED . All courses must be taken for a letter grade. For more information regarding this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit https:// chemistry.ucla.edu and https:// admission.ucla.edu. PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation requirements for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed.",
    "UCLA's Chem 153A and/or 153L are upper-division courses that satisfy major requirements but are NOT required for admission. After transferring, students must petition for transfer credit and should contact the academic advisor for their major for additional support and details about this process.",
    "The AP Scores listed below may be used to satisfy the major prep: A score of 4 or higher on the AP Chemistry exam can be used in place of CHEM 20A ONLY. A score of 5 on the AP Calculus AB exam will satisfy MATH 31A. A score of 4 on the AP Calculus BC exam will satisfy MATH 31A. A score of 5 on the AP Calculus BC exam will satisfy MATH 31A and 31B. The IB Exam Scores listed below may be used to satisfy the major prep: A score of 6 or higher on the IB HL Chemistry exam can be used in place of CHEM 20A ONLY. A score of 6 or higher on the IB HL Math Analysis & Approaches exam will satisfy MATH 31A."
  ]
